Activity: A16 - Discover 3 local security incidents

Objective
The goal of this activity was to research and identify recent cybersecurty incidents that occurred in Australia to understand real=world threats and their impact.

Method
I researched recent Australian cybersecurity incidents using online news sources and cybersecurity repots to identify major breaches affecting organisations and individuals.

Findings
The following local security incidents were identified:
1. Optus data breach - personal data of millions of customers was exposed, including names, addresses, and identification documents. the breach occurred due to an unsecured API.
2. Medibacnk cyberattack - hackers accessed sensitive health and personal data of customers. the attackers demanded a ransom, and when it was not paid, the data was leaked online
3. Latitude financial data breach - millions of customer records were stolen, including driver's licence and passport details, due to compromised employee credentials.

Security Principle
These incidents highlight the importance of confidentiality, integrity, and availability. protecting sensitive user data, prventing unauthorised access, and maintainingsecure systems are critical in mdoern cybersecurity.

